xt","value":". Currently, machine learning is even the main representation of artificial intelligence with ","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"key":"iNDE0cUQpz"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"deep learning","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"key":"K56F80aJH0"}],"key":"iD5dD2RrRC"},{"type":"text","value":" being the most prominent subset. Here, however, we will focus on more classical machine learning techniques (no worries, those remain equally important in real-life practice!).","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"key":"YDr4CaS3n8"}],"key":"Smn8M6XnX9"}],"key":"LJTua7yhZD"}],"label":"fig_ai_vs_ml_vs_dl","identifier":"fig_ai_vs_ml_vs_dl","enumerator":"1","html_id":"fig-ai-vs-ml-vs-dl","key":"HhQ1Y4XvvR"}],"key":"OwgmyG9iER"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The key idea behind machine learning is that we use algorithms that ","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"fMHd8bnwDC"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“learn from data”","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"aOJaxTnhd9"}],"key":"iLxmN0ArKF"},{"type":"text","value":". Learning here is nothing magic and typically means something very different from our everyday use of the word “learning” in a human context. Learning here simply means that the rules by which a program decides on its outcome or behavior are no longer ","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"wU9xPlG3YQ"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}}