supervised Learning","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"NfRujBYFUY"}],"key":"O1xF7x0PWx"},{"type":"text","value":", on the other hand, involves training a model on data that does not have labeled responses. The goal here is to infer the natural structure present within a set of data points. This is often used for clustering and association problems. An example of unsupervised learning is customer segmentation, where the model identifies distinct groups of customers based on purchasing behavior without prior knowledge of the group definitions.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"j7EqYr6LPc"}],"key":"n1lfauit2I"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Wait. That sounds familiar, right?","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"Fs6zD9su0b"},{"type":"break","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"DI5BZQJNOr"},{"type":"text","value":"And indeed, this is exactly what we covered in the prior sections! Many algorithms used in dimensionality reduction (","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"mAXmgFXBHm"},{"type":"link","kind":"ref","identifier":"ch_dimensionality","label":"ch_dimensionality","url":"/notebooks/dimensionality-reduction","internal":true,"dataUrl":"/notebooks.dimensionality-reduction.json","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Dimensionality Reduction","key":"mdzKNewMtT"}],"key":"UQup0BsAgh"},{"type":"text","value":") and clustering (","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"BWjts756Yu"},{"type":"link","kind":"ref","identifier":"ch_clustering","label":"ch_clustering","url":"/notebooks/clustering","internal":true,"dataUrl":"/notebooks.clustering.json","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Clustering","key":"XXDKm4d28u"}],"key":"WylYiJWu